  Easy HTML Construction Kit provides an easy way to create the HTML code for
  lists and tables, and to convert data in textfiles (such as archives of
  mailing lists) to lists, tables and full HTML documents. It comprises six
  separate utility programs.
  
  To use Easy HTML Construction Kit to assist in the writing of web pages you
  need only a basic knowledge of HTML. You should be able to do simple editing,
  such as knowing how to use &lt;BR&gt; and &lt;P&gt; tags, and you should be able to
  recognize the start and end of HTML code for lists (&lt;UL&gt;...&lt;/UL&gt;, &lt;OL&gt;...&lt;/OL&gt;)
  and tables (&lt;TABLE&gt;...&lt;/TABLE&gt;), but you don't need to know much more. If you
  can already do basic HTML programming then Easy HTML Construction Kit will
  allow you to do it better and much more quickly, and will allow construction
  of tables too tricky to do by hand coding (such as the table above).
  
  The HTML code produced by Easy HTML Construction Kit conforms to the HTML 3.2
  standard. No use is made of HTML 4.0 tags or of advanced techniques such as
  cascading style sheets. Thus the HTML code produced works with all major web
  browsers and the program produces HTML code for lists and tables which look
  very similar on all browsers.
  
  When converting data contained in an input text file there is no limit on the
  input file size, but input and output files can be displayed by the program
  only for files of not more than 40 KB in size. Output HTML files can be
  displayed in a web browser from within the program, and in this case there is
  no restriction on file size.

  --------------
  Unzip, install the program, run the keygen to make reginfo, and use it to
  register the program.
